2026-04-16 12:18:10 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 6 internal series path between Control Input Cable (+) 6 port p and Control Output Cable (+) 6 (including the switch contacts and any internal wiring links)'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show 12 V present at Control Input (+) 6 port p, but that node is floating internally and no voltage appears at Control Output (+/−) 6. All upstream modules pass 12 V correctly and there is no polarity inversion. Downstream modules and the load see 0 V only because Control Module 6 does not propagate the series path. This indicates an open circuit fault inside Control Module 6’s main series path (e.g., broken trace, disconnected wire, or failed switch contact) between the input positive terminal and the output positive terminal, while the negative side remains continuous. Repairing or replacing that internal series path in Control Module 6 should restore voltage to the subsequent modules and allow the lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
