description: Open the inspection panel of Control Module 6 and, with battery inserted and all switches ON, (1) visually trace which external cables form the incoming and outgoing series pair and which go to the LED branch; (2) using a voltmeter, measure continuity and DC voltage across the internal series path from its input (+/−) terminals to its output (+/−) terminals to see whether the switch and wiring pass 12 V through when ON, and check for any open circuit, mis‑wiring, or missing links; (3) note whether the indicator LED branch is present or missing, but focus on verifying that the main series path is intact and correctly routed to the output cables., outcome='Control Module 6 has its incoming series pair as Control Input Cables (+/−) 6, and its outgoing series pair as Control Output Cables (+/−) 6, with no POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED between any (+) and (−) cables. The main series path does not pass 12 V through to the output: Control Input Cable (+) 6 has 11.99 V on port p but its port n is floating and the Control Output Cables (+/−) 6 both read 0 V. The indicator LED branch (Power Flow Indicator (green) 6 and its resistor) is completely missing.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=265.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
